article.description: Malcolm Regisford had 13 points and 10 rebounds and Colgate used a big second half to pull away from New Hampshire 75-59 on Sunday.
article.headline: Colgate uses big 2nd half to beat New Hampshire 75-59
article.linkText: Colgate uses big 2nd half to beat New Hampshire 75-59
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Malcolm Regisford had 13 points and 10 rebounds and Colgate used a big second half to pull away from New Hampshire 75-59 on Sunday. Jordan Robertson scored 15 points, Tom Rivard added 13, and Austin Tillotson contributed 10 assists for the Raiders (4-6), who made 11 of 28 (39 percent) 3-pointers. Tied at 27 at halftime, New Hampshire pulled ahead 37-33 after Iba Camara's jumper, but Colgate took the lead 49-40 midway through the second half on a 14-3 run in which Alex Ramon made two 3-pointers. Robertson scored five points in an 11-2 Raiders run and Colgate pulled away 70-52 with 3:16 left. The Raiders outscored the Wildcats 48-32 in the second half and made 29 of 61 field goals (48 percent). Camara and Daniel Dion scored 16 points apiece for New Hampshire (6-4), which shot 40 percent from the field.
